<section class="content-section" id="how-to-use"><h2>How to Use the ROC Filing Calendar</h2><p>Select your entity type and the calendar auto-populates all applicable filings for FY 2025-26 based on <a href="https://www.mca.gov.in/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">MCA</a> regulations. Cards are colour-coded: red for overdue filings, amber for due within 30 days, and green for upcoming. Each card shows the form name, description, due date, and applicable penalty for late filing.</p><div class="callout"><p><strong>CA Tip:</strong> Set reminders 30 days before each deadline. Non-filing for 3+ consecutive years leads to company strike-off and director disqualification under <a href="https://www.indiacode.nic.in/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Companies Act 2013</a> Section 248. The <a href="https://www.icai.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ICAI</a> recommends a compliance calendar approach for all companies.</p></div></section>

<section class="content-section" id="penalties"><h2>Late Filing Penalty Structure</h2><div style="overflow-x:auto;"><table class="rate-table"><thead><tr><th>Delay Period</th><th>Company (AOC-4/MGT-7A)</th><th>LLP (Form 8/11)</th><th>DIR-3 KYC</th></tr></thead><tbody>
<tr><td>Up to 30 days</td><td>2&times; normal fee</td><td>&#8377;100/day</td><td>&#8377;5,000 flat</td></tr>
<tr><td>30&ndash;60 days</td><td>4&times; normal fee</td><td>&#8377;100/day</td><td>DIN deactivated</td></tr>
<tr><td>60&ndash;90 days</td><td>6&times; normal fee</td><td>&#8377;100/day</td><td>DIN deactivated</td></tr>
<tr><td>Beyond 90 days</td><td>10&times; normal fee</td><td>&#8377;100/day (no cap)</td><td>DIN deactivated</td></tr>
<tr><td>3+ years non-filing</td><td>Strike-off + disqualification</td><td>Strike-off</td><td>N/A</td></tr>
</tbody></table></div></section>

<section class="content-section" id="pvt-ltd"><h2>Pvt Ltd / OPC Annual Filings Checklist</h2><ul><li><strong>AOC-4:</strong> Financial statements filing within 30 days of AGM (by ~Oct 29)</li><li><strong>MGT-7A:</strong> Annual return within 60 days of AGM (by ~Nov 28)</li><li><strong>DIR-3 KYC:</strong> Director KYC by September 30 every year</li><li><strong>ADT-1:</strong> Auditor appointment within 15 days of AGM</li><li><strong>ITR-6:</strong> Income tax return by September 30 (audit cases)</li><li><strong>GSTR-9:</strong> GST annual return by December 31</li><li><strong>Board Meetings:</strong> Minimum 4 per year, max 120-day gap</li><li><strong>AGM:</strong> Within 6 months of FY end (by September 30)</li></ul></section>

<section class="content-section" id="llp"><h2>LLP Annual Filings Checklist</h2><ul><li><strong>Form 8:</strong> Statement of Account &amp; Solvency by October 30</li><li><strong>Form 11:</strong> Annual Return by May 30</li><li><strong>DIR-3 KYC:</strong> Partner KYC by September 30</li><li><strong>ITR-5:</strong> By September 30 (if audit applicable) or July 31</li><li><strong>GSTR-9:</strong> GST annual return by December 31</li></ul></section>

<div class="callout" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#EFF6FF,#F0F7FF);border-left-color:var(--primary);margin:0 0 32px;"><p style="color:var(--primary-dark);font-size:15px;"><strong>Never miss a filing!</strong> Our CAs handle complete annual compliance for Pvt Ltd, OPC, and LLP. ROC filings, audit, ITR, GST &mdash; all managed. <a href="https://wa.me/919459456700?text=Hi%20Patron%20Accounting%2C%20I%20need%20annual%20ROC%20compliance%20help." target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:var(--primary);font-weight:700;">Talk to a CA today &rarr;</a></p></div>

